@theme @theme_charteredcollege @theme_charteredcollege_personalmenu
Feature: When the moodle theme is set to charteredcollege, personal menu's login form has https action.

  Background:
    Given the following "users" exist:
      | username | firstname | lastname | email                |
      | teacher1 | Teacher   | 1        | teacher1@example.com |
    Given the following config values are set as admin:
      | loginhttps | 1 |

  @javascript
  Scenario: User login form uses https when loginhttps is enabled
    Given I am on site homepage
    And I follow "Log in"
    Then ".charteredcollege-pm-content > form[action*='https']" "css_element" should be visible
